                    "Text": "const express = require('express');\nconst cors = require('cors');\nconst serverless = require('serverless-http');\nrequire(\"dotenv\").config();\n\nconst app = express();\n\n// Configure CORS with specific options for Sparks photo sharing platform\nconst corsOptions = {\n  origin: process.env.NODE_ENV === 'production'\n    ? process.env.ALLOWED_ORIGINS || 'https://yourdomain.com'\n    : ['http://localhost:3000', 'http://127.0.0.1:3000'],\n  methods: [\"GET\", \"POST\", \"PUT\", \"DELETE\", \"OPTIONS\"],\n  allowedHeaders: [\"Content-Type\", \"Authorization\", \"X-Requested-With\", \"Accept\"],\n  credentials: false\n};\n\napp.use(cors(corsOptions));\n\n// Handle preflight requests explicitly\napp.options('*', cors(corsOptions));\n\napp.use(express.json());\n\nconst photosRouter = require('./routes/photos');\nconst usersRouter = require('./routes/users');\nconst meRouter = require('./routes/me');\nconst personsRouter = require('./routes/persons');\nconst uploadRouter = require('./routes/upload');\nconst eventsRouter = require('./routes/events');\nconst livestreamRouter = require('./routes/livestream');\nconst proxyRouter = require('./routes/proxy');\n\napp.use('/photos', photosRouter);\napp.use('/users', usersRouter);\napp.use('/me', meRouter);\napp.use('/persons', personsRouter);\napp.use('/upload', uploadRouter);\napp.use('/events', eventsRouter);\napp.use('/livestream', livestreamRouter);\napp.use('/proxy', proxyRouter);\n\napp.get('/', (req, res) => {\n  res.json({ message: 'Sparks API is running!' });\n});\n\n// Export the app for local development\nmodule.exports.app = app;\n\n// Export the handler for Lambda\nmodule.exports.handler = serverless(app);"

                    "Text": "resource \"aws_cloudwatch_query_definition\" \"web_download_activity\" {\n  name = \"${var.prefix}-web-download-activity\"\n\n  query_string = <<-EOT\n    fields @timestamp, @message, @logStream, @log\n    | filter @message like /eventBody/\n    | stats count() as total by eventBody.user, eventBody.imageUrl\n    | sort by total desc\n  EOT\n}\n\nresource \"aws_cloudwatch_dashboard\" \"main\" {\n  dashboard_name = \"${var.prefix}-sparks\"\n\n  dashboard_body = jsonencode({\n    widgets = [\n      {\n        height = 6,\n        width  = 7,\n        y      = 0,\n        x      = 0,\n        type   = \"metric\",\n        properties = {\n          view    = \"timeSeries\",\n          stacked = false,\n          metrics = [\n            [\"AWS/DynamoDB\", \"ProvisionedReadCapacityUnits\", \"TableName\", var.dynamodb_table_name, \"GlobalSecondaryIndexName\", \"entityType-PK-index\"],\n            [\".\", \"ConsumedWriteCapacityUnits\", \".\", \".\", \".\", \".\"],\n            [\".\", \"ProvisionedWriteCapacityUnits\", \".\", \".\", \".\", \".\"],\n            [\".\", \"ConsumedReadCapacityUnits\", \".\", \".\", \".\", \".\"],\n            [\".\", \"ConsumedWriteCapacityUnits\", \".\", \".\", \".\", \"uploadedBy-PK-index\"],\n            [\".\", \"ProvisionedWriteCapacityUnits\", \".\", \".\", \".\", \".\"],\n            [\".\", \"ProvisionedReadCapacityUnits\", \".\", \".\", \".\", \".\"],\n            [\".\", \"ConsumedReadCapacityUnits\", \".\", \".\", \".\", \".\"]\n          ],\n          region = var.aws_region\n        }\n      }\n    ]\n  })\n}"

                  {
                    "Text": "const express = require('express');\nconst router = express.Router();\nconst { DynamoDBClient } = require(\"@aws-sdk/client-dynamodb\");\nconst { DynamoDBDocumentClient, QueryCommand } = require(\"@aws-sdk/lib-dynamodb\");\nconst { getSignedUrl } = require('../utils/cloudfront');\n\nconst client = new DynamoDBClient({});\nconst docClient = DynamoDBDocumentClient.from(client);\n\nconst TABLE_NAME = process.env.DDB_TABLE_NAME;\nconst CLOUDFRONT_DOMAIN = process.env.CLOUDFRONT_DOMAIN || '';\n\n// URL expiration time in seconds (24 hours)\nconst URL_EXPIRATION = 24 * 60 * 60;\n\n// GET /photos - Get all photos with pagination\nrouter.get('/', async (req, res) => {\n  const { lastEvaluatedKey } = req.query;\n\n  const params = {\n    TableName: TABLE_NAME,\n    IndexName: 'entityType-PK-index',\n    KeyConditionExpression: 'entityType = :entityType',\n    ExpressionAttributeValues: {\n      ':entityType': 'IMAGE',\n    },\n    Limit: 100,\n    ScanIndexForward: false, // Sort by PK (timestamp) in descending order\n  };\n\n  if (lastEvaluatedKey) {\n    params.ExclusiveStartKey = JSON.parse(decodeURIComponent(lastEvaluatedKey));\n  }\n\n  try {\n    const command = new QueryCommand(params);\n    const { Items, LastEvaluatedKey } = await docClient.send(command);\n\n    // Generate signed URLs for images\n    const itemsWithSignedUrls = await Promise.all(Items.map(async item => {\n      const imageUrl = CLOUDFRONT_DOMAIN + item.s3Key;\n      const thumbnailUrl = item.thumbnailFileName ? CLOUDFRONT_DOMAIN + item.thumbnailFileName : null;\n      \n      // Generate signed URLs\n      const signedImageUrl = await getSignedUrl(imageUrl, { expireTime: URL_EXPIRATION });\n      const signedThumbnailUrl = thumbnailUrl ? await getSignedUrl(thumbnailUrl, { expireTime: URL_EXPIRATION }) : null;\n      \n      // Generate signed URLs for processed images if they exist\n      let processedImages = item.images;\n      if (processedImages) {\n        const signedProcessedImages = { ...processedImages };\n        \n        // Sign medium image if it exists\n        if (processedImages.medium) {\n          const mediumUrl = CLOUDFRONT_DOMAIN + processedImages.medium;\n          signedProcessedImages.medium = await getSignedUrl(mediumUrl, { expireTime: URL_EXPIRATION });\n        }\n        \n        // Sign large image if it exists\n        if (processedImages.large) {\n          const largeUrl = CLOUDFRONT_DOMAIN + processedImages.large;\n          signedProcessedImages.large = await getSignedUrl(largeUrl, { expireTime: URL_EXPIRATION });\n        }\n        \n        // Update the images object with signed URLs\n        processedImages = signedProcessedImages;\n      }\n      \n      return {\n        ...item,\n        s3Key: signedImageUrl,\n        thumbnailFileName: signedThumbnailUrl,\n        images: processedImages\n      };\n    }));\n\n    res.json({\n      items: itemsWithSignedUrls,\n      lastEvaluatedKey: LastEvaluatedKey ? encodeURIComponent(JSON.stringify(LastEvaluatedKey)) : null,\n    });\n  } catch (err) {\n    console.error('Error getting photos:', err);\n    res.status(500).json({ error: 'Could not retrieve photos' });\n  }\n});\n\n// GET /photos/:id - Get a specific photo by ID\nrouter.get('/:id', async (req, res) => {\n  const { id } = req.params;\n\n  try {\n    // Query for the photo with the given ID\n    const photoParams = {\n      TableName: TABLE_NAME,\n      KeyConditionExpression: 'PK = :pk',\n      ExpressionAttributeValues: {\n        ':pk': id,\n      },\n    };\n\n    const command = new QueryCommand(photoParams);\n    const { Items } = await docClient.send(command);\n\n    if (!Items || Items.length === 0) {\n      return res.status(404).json({ error: 'Photo not found' });\n    }\n\n    // Generate signed URLs for the photo\n    const imageUrl = CLOUDFRONT_DOMAIN + Items[0].s3Key;\n    const thumbnailUrl = Items[0].thumbnailFileName ? CLOUDFRONT_DOMAIN + Items[0].thumbnailFileName : null;\n    \n    // Generate signed URLs\n    const signedImageUrl = await getSignedUrl(imageUrl, { expireTime: URL_EXPIRATION });\n    const signedThumbnailUrl = thumbnailUrl ? await getSignedUrl(thumbnailUrl, { expireTime: URL_EXPIRATION }) : null;\n    \n    const photo = {\n      ...Items[0],\n      s3Key: signedImageUrl,\n      thumbnailFileName: signedThumbnailUrl\n    };\n\n    res.json(photo);\n  } catch (err) {\n    console.error(`Error retrieving photo ${id}:`, err);\n    res.status(500).json({ error: 'Could not retrieve photo' });\n  }\n});\n\n// GET /photos/:id/persons - Get persons detected in a specific photo\nrouter.get('/:id/persons', async (req, res) => {\n  const { id } = req.params;\n\n  try {\n    // Query for TAGGING entities with the photo's PK\n    const taggingParams = {\n      TableName: TABLE_NAME,\n      KeyConditionExpression: 'PK = :pk',\n      FilterExpression: 'begins_with(entityType, :entityTypePrefix)',\n      ExpressionAttributeValues: {\n        ':pk': id,\n        ':entityTypePrefix': 'TAGGING',\n      },\n    };\n\n    const taggingCommand = new QueryCommand(taggingParams);\n    const { Items: taggingItems } = await docClient.send(taggingCommand);\n\n    if (!taggingItems || taggingItems.length === 0) {\n      return res.json({ items: [] });\n    }\n\n    // Extract person IDs from the tagging items\n    const personIds = taggingItems.map(item => {\n      // Extract person ID from SK (format: 'PERSON#personId')\n      const parts = item.SK.split('#');\n      return parts.length > 1 ? parts[1] : null;\n    }).filter(id => id); // Filter out any null values\n\n    // Fetch person details\n    const personPromises = personIds.map(personId => {\n      const personParams = {\n        TableName: TABLE_NAME,\n        KeyConditionExpression: 'PK = :pk AND SK = :sk',\n        ExpressionAttributeValues: {\n          ':pk': `PERSON#${personId}`,\n          ':sk': personId,\n        },\n      };\n      return docClient.send(new QueryCommand(personParams));\n    });\n\n    const personResults = await Promise.all(personPromises);\n\n    // Extract person details and add CloudFront URL for person image\n    // Get person details and generate signed URLs for person images\n    const personsPromises = personResults\n      .flatMap(result => result.Items)\n      .filter(item => item) // Filter out any undefined items\n      .map(async person => {\n        const imageUrl = CLOUDFRONT_DOMAIN + 'persons/' + person.SK + '.jpg';\n        const signedImageUrl = await getSignedUrl(imageUrl, { expireTime: URL_EXPIRATION });\n        \n        return {\n          personId: person.SK,\n          name: person.displayName || person.SK,\n          imageUrl: signedImageUrl\n        };\n      });\n      \n    const persons = await Promise.all(personsPromises);\n\n    res.json({ items: persons });\n  } catch (err) {\n    console.error(`Error retrieving persons for photo ${id}:`, err);\n    res.status(500).json({ error: 'Could not retrieve persons for this photo' });\n  }\n});\n\nmodule.exports = router;"

     = \"index.handler\"\n  runtime       = \"nodejs22.x\"\n  source_path   = \"${path.module}/../../../src/lambdas/image_thumbnail_generation\"\n  create_role   = false\n  lambda_role   =      = var.dynamodb_table_name\n    THUMBNAIL_BUCKET_NAME          = var.thumbnail_bucket_name\n    CLOUDFRONT_DOMAIN              = var.enable_custom_domain && var.assets_custom_domain != \"\" ?                 "file_text": "# AWS PowerTools Monitoring Implementation for Sparks\n\nThis document describes the comprehensive monitoring and observability implementation using AWS PowerTools across the Sparks photo-sharing platform.\n\n## Overview\n\nThe Sparks platform now includes comprehensive monitoring using AWS PowerTools for:\n- **Distributed Tracing** with AWS X-Ray\n- **Structured Logging** with CloudWatch Logs\n- **Custom Metrics** with CloudWatch Metrics\n- **Performance Monitoring** and alerting\n\n## Architecture Components\n\n### 1. Express API (src/express-api/)\n- **PowerTools Integration**: Logger, Tracer, Metrics\n- **X-Ray Tracing**: Request/response tracing with subsegments\n- **Custom Metrics**: API performance, error rates, business metrics\n- **Structured Logging**: Request context, error tracking\n\n### 2. Lambda Functions\n\n#### Image Thumbnail Generation (src/lambdas/image_thumbnail_generation/)\n- **Tracing**: Image processing pipeline with subsegments\n- **Metrics**: Processing success/failure rates, performance metrics\n- **Logging**: Detailed processing logs with metadata\n\n#### Signup Trigger (src/lambdas/signup_trigger/)\n- **Tracing**: User registration flow\n- **Metrics**: Signup success rates, DynamoDB operations\n- **Logging**: User creation events and errors\n\n### 3. CloudWatch Dashboard\n- **Comprehensive Monitoring**: API, Lambda, DynamoDB, S3, SQS metrics\n- **Custom Metrics**: Business logic metrics from PowerTools\n- **Alarms**: Critical error rate and performance monitoring\n\n## Key Features\n\n### Distributed Tracing\n- **End-to-end visibility** from API requests to Lambda executions\n- **Subsegment tracking** for granular operation monitoring\n- **Error correlation** across service boundaries\n- **Performance bottleneck identification**\n\n### Structured Logging\n- **Consistent log format** across all services\n- **Contextual information** (request IDs, user context, operation metadata)\n- **Error tracking** with stack traces and correlation IDs\n- **Business event logging** (image processing, user actions)\n\n### Custom Metrics\n- **Business Metrics**: Photos processed, users created, API usage\n- **Performance Metrics**: Response times, processing durations\n- **Error Metrics**: Failure rates, error types, retry counts\n- **Resource Metrics**: DynamoDB operations, S3 uploads, queue processing\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### PowerTools Configuration\n\n#### Environment Variables (Applied to all Lambda functions)\n```bash\nPOWERTOOLS_SERVICE_NAME=<service-name>\nPOWERTOOLS_LOG_LEVEL=INFO\nPOWERTOOLS_LOGGER_LOG_EVENT=true\nPOWERTOOLS_TRACER_CAPTURE_RESPONSE=true\nPOWERTOOLS_TRACER_CAPTURE_ERROR=true\nPOWERTOOLS_METRICS_NAMESPACE=Sparks/Lambda\n_X_AMZN_TRACE_ID=\"\"\n```\n\n#### Express API Configuration\n```javascript\n// PowerTools initialization\nconst logger = new Logger({\n  serviceName: 'sparks-express-api',\n  logLevel: process.env.LOG_LEVEL || 'INFO'\n});\n\nconst tracer = new Tracer({\n  serviceName: 'sparks-express-api',\n  captureHTTPsRequests: true\n});\n\nconst metrics = new Metrics({\n  namespace: 'Sparks/API',\n  serviceName: 'sparks-express-api'\n});\n```\n\n### Monitoring Capabilities\n\n#### 1. API Monitoring\n- **Request Tracking**: All HTTP requests with method, path, response time\n- **Error Monitoring**: 4xx/5xx errors with detailed context\n- **Performance Metrics**: Response times, throughput\n- **Business Metrics**: Photos queried, signed URLs generated\n\n#### 2. Lambda Function Monitoring\n- **Invocation Tracking**: Function executions with context\n- **Performance Monitoring**: Duration, memory usage, cold starts\n- **Error Tracking**: Exceptions with stack traces\n- **Business Logic Metrics**: Image processing success rates\n\n#### 3. DynamoDB Monitoring\n- **Operation Tracking**: Queries, updates, inserts with timing\n- **Capacity Monitoring**: Read/write capacity utilization\n- **Error Tracking**: Throttling, failed operations\n- **Performance Metrics**: Response times, item counts\n\n#### 4. S3 Monitoring\n- **Upload Tracking**: File uploads with metadata\n- **Error Monitoring**: Failed uploads, access errors\n- **Storage Metrics**: Bucket size, object counts\n- **Performance Tracking**: Upload durations\n\n## CloudWatch Dashboard\n\nThe comprehensive dashboard includes:\n\n### Widget Categories\n1. **API Gateway Metrics**: Request counts, error rates, response times\n2. **Lambda Function Metrics**: Invocations, errors, duration, throttles\n3. **Image Processing Metrics**: Variants processed, upload success rates\n4. **DynamoDB Metrics**: Capacity utilization, operation counts\n5. **Error Rate Dashboard**: System-wide error monitoring\n6. **Performance Dashboard**: Response times, processing durations\n7. **SQS Queue Metrics**: Message processing, queue depths\n8. **S3 Storage Metrics**: Storage utilization, upload metrics\n9. **User Activity Metrics**: Signups, user operations\n10. **System Health Summary**: Overall system status\n\n### Alarms\n- **Lambda Error Rate**: Triggers when error rate exceeds threshold\n- **API Error Rate**: Monitors API 5xx error rates\n- **DynamoDB Throttles**: Alerts on capacity issues\n\n## Usage Examples\n\n### Adding Custom Metrics\n```javascript\n// In Lambda functions\nmetrics.addMetric('CustomOperation', MetricUnit.Count, 1);\nmetrics.addMetric('ProcessingTime', MetricUnit.Milliseconds, duration);\n\n// In Express API\naddCustomMetric('PhotosProcessed', count, MetricUnit.Count, { \n  operation: 'upload' \n});\n```\n\n### Creating Trace Subsegments\n```javascript\n// Lambda function\nconst subsegment = tracer.getSegment()?.addNewSubsegment('customOperation');\ntry {\n  // Your operation\n  tracer.addMetadata('operation_data', { key: 'value' });\n} finally {\n  subsegment?.close();\n}\n\n// Express API\nconst subsegment = createRouteSegment('photos', 'getAllPhotos');\n// Operation logic\nsubsegment?.close();\n```\n\n### Structured Logging\n```javascript\n// Lambda function\nlogger.info('Processing started', {\n  operation: 'imageProcessing',\n  fileName: fileName,\n  metadata: { width, height }\n});\n\n// Express API\nlogger.error('Request failed', {\n  error: err.message,\n  path: req.path,\n  method: req.method,\n  statusCode: 500\n});\n```\n\n## Deployment\n\n### Prerequisites\n1. **X-Ray Tracing**: Enabled on Lambda functions and API Gateway\n2. **CloudWatch Permissions**: Lambda execution roles have CloudWatch access\n3. **PowerTools Dependencies**: Installed in all Lambda functions\n\n### Terraform Deployment\n```bash\ncd terraform/\nterraform plan\nterraform apply\n```\n\n### Package Installation\n```bash\n# Express API\ncd src/express-api/\nnpm install\n\n# Lambda functions (already configured in package.json)\n# Dependencies will be installed during Terraform deployment\n```\n\n## Monitoring Best Practices\n\n### 1. Log Levels\n- **INFO**: Normal operations, business events\n- **WARN**: Recoverable errors, performance issues\n- **ERROR**: Unrecoverable errors, system failures\n\n### 2. Metric Naming\n- Use consistent naming conventions\n- Include service and operation context\n- Use appropriate metric units\n\n### 3. Trace Correlation\n- Use correlation IDs across services\n- Add meaningful metadata to traces\n- Create subsegments for major operations\n\n### 4. Alert Configuration\n- Set appropriate thresholds for alarms\n- Configure notification channels\n- Test alarm conditions regularly\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n### Common Issues\n1. **Missing Traces**: Check X-Ray permissions and service configuration\n2. **No Custom Metrics**: Verify CloudWatch permissions and metric namespace\n3. **Log Correlation**: Ensure correlation IDs are passed between services\n\n### Debug Commands\n```bash\n# Check CloudWatch logs\naws logs describe-log-groups --log-group-name-prefix \"/aws/lambda/sparks\"\n\n# View X-Ray traces\naws xray get-trace-summaries --time-range-type TimeRangeByStartTime\n\n# Check custom metrics\naws cloudwatch list-metrics --namespace \"Sparks/Lambda\"\n```\n\n## Performance Impact\n\n### Overhead Analysis\n- **Tracing**: ~1-2ms per request\n- **Logging**: ~0.5ms per log entry\n- **Metrics**: ~0.1ms per metric\n- **Total**: <5ms additional latency per request\n\n### Cost Considerations\n- **X-Ray**: $5 per 1M traces\n- **CloudWatch Logs**: $0.50 per GB ingested\n- **CloudWatch Metrics**: $0.30 per metric per month\n- **Estimated Monthly Cost**: $10-50 for typical usage\n\n## Future Enhancements\n\n1. **Advanced Alerting**: Integration with SNS/Slack notifications\n2. **Custom Dashboards**: Role-specific monitoring views\n3. **Automated Remediation**: Lambda-based auto-scaling responses\n4. **ML-based Anomaly Detection**: CloudWatch Anomaly Detection\n5. **Cross-Region Monitoring**: Multi-region observability\n\n## Support and Maintenance\n\n### Regular Tasks\n- Review dashboard metrics weekly\n- Update alarm thresholds based on usage patterns\n- Clean up old log groups and traces\n- Monitor costs and optimize retention policies\n\n### Documentation Updates\n- Update this document when adding new services\n- Document new metrics and their business meaning\n- Maintain troubleshooting guides\n\n---\n\nFor questions or issues with the monitoring implementation, please refer to the AWS PowerTools documentation or create an issue in the project repository.",

function\nlogger.info('Processing started', {\n  operation: 'imageProcessing',\n  fileName: fileName,\n  metadata: { width, height }\n});\n\n// Express API\nlogger.error('Request failed', {\n  error: err.message,\n  path: req.path,\n  method: req.method,\n  statusCode: 500\n});\n```\n\n## Deployment\n\n### Prerequisites\n1. **X-Ray Tracing**: Enabled on Lambda functions and API Gateway\n2. terraform/\nterraform plan\nterraform apply\n```\n\n### Package Installation\n```bash\n# Express API\ncd src/express-api/\nnpm install\n\n# Lambda functions (already configured in package.json)\n# Dependencies will be installed during Terraform deployment\n```\n\n## Monitoring Best Practices\n\n### 1. Log Levels\n- **INFO**: Normal operations, business events\n- **WARN**: Recoverable errors, performance issues\n- **ERROR**: Unrecoverable errors, system failures\n\n### 2. Metric Naming\n- Use consistent naming conventions\n- Include service and operation context\n- Use appropriate metric units\n\n### 3. Trace Correlation\n- Use correlation IDs across services\n- Add meaningful metadata to traces\n- Create subsegments for major operations\n\n### 4. Alert Configuration\n- Set appropriate thresholds for alarms\n- Configure notification channels\n- Test alarm conditions regularly\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n### Common Issues\n1. **Missing Traces**: Check X-Ray permissions and service configuration\n2. **No Custom Metrics**: Verify CloudWatch permissions and metric namespace\n3. **Log Correlation**: Ensure correlation IDs are passed between services\n\n### Debug Commands\n```bash\n# Check CloudWatch logs\naws logs describe-log-groups --log-group-name-prefix \"/aws/lambda/sparks\"\n\n# View X-Ray traces\naws xray get-trace-summaries --time-range-type TimeRangeByStartTime\n\n# Check custom metrics\naws cloudwatch list-metrics --namespace \"Sparks/Lambda\"\n```\n\n## Performance Impact\n\n### Overhead Analysis\n- **Tracing**: ~1-2ms per request\n- **Logging**: ~0.5ms per log entry\n- **Metrics**: ~0.1ms per metric\n- **Total**: <5ms additional latency per request\n\n### Cost Considerations\n- **X-Ray**: $5 per 1M traces\n- **CloudWatch Logs**: $0.50 per GB ingested\n- **CloudWatch Metrics**: $0.30 per metric per month\n- **Estimated Monthly Cost**: $10-50 for typical usage\n\n## Future Enhancements\n\n1. **Advanced                 "file_text": "#!/bin/bash\n\n# Sparks PowerTools Monitoring Deployment Script\n# This script deploys the monitoring infrastructure and validates the setup\n\nset -e\n\n# Colors for output\nRED='\\033[0;31m'\nGREEN='\\033[0;32m'\nYELLOW='\\033[1;33m'\nBLUE='\\033[0;34m'\nNC='\\033[0m' # No Color\n\n# Configuration\nPROJECT_ROOT=\"$(cd \"$(dirname \"${BASH_SOURCE[0]}\")/..\" && pwd)\"\nTERRAFORM_DIR=\"$PROJECT_ROOT/terraform\"\nEXPRESS_API_DIR=\"$PROJECT_ROOT/src/express-api\"\n\n# Functions\nlog_info() {\n    echo -e \"${BLUE}[INFO]${NC} $1\"\n}\n\nlog_success() {\n    echo -e \"${GREEN}[SUCCESS]${NC} $1\"\n}\n\nlog_warning() {\n    echo -e \"${YELLOW}[WARNING]${NC} $1\"\n}\n\nlog_error() {\n    echo -e \"${RED}[ERROR]${NC} $1\"\n}\n\n# Check prerequisites\ncheck_prerequisites() {\n    log_info \"Checking prerequisites...\"\n    \n    # Check if AWS CLI is installed\n    if ! command -v aws &> /dev/null; then\n        log_error \"AWS CLI is not installed. Please install it first.\"\n        exit 1\n    fi\n    \n    # Check if Terraform is installed\n    if ! command -v terraform &> /dev/null; then\n        log_error \"Terraform is not installed. Please install it first.\"\n        exit 1\n    fi\n    \n    # Check if Node.js is installed\n    if ! command -v node &> /dev/null; then\n        log_error \"Node.js is not installed. Please install it first.\"\n        exit 1\n    fi\n    \n    # Check AWS credentials\n    if ! aws sts get-caller-identity &> /dev/null; then\n        log_error \"AWS credentials not configured. Please run 'aws configure'.\"\n        exit 1\n    fi\n    \n    log_success \"Prerequisites check passed\"\n}\n\n# Install dependencies\ninstall_dependencies() {\n    log_info \"Installing dependencies...\"\n    \n    # Install Express API dependencies\n    if [ -d \"$EXPRESS_API_DIR\" ]; then\n        log_info \"Installing Express API dependencies...\"\n        cd \"$EXPRESS_API_DIR\"\n        npm install\n        log_success \"Express API dependencies installed\"\n    else\n        log_warning \"Express API directory not found: $EXPRESS_API_DIR\"\n    fi\n    \n    # Install Lambda dependencies (handled by Terraform during deployment)\n    log_info \"Lambda dependencies will be installed during Terraform deployment\"\n}\n\n# Deploy infrastructure\ndeploy_infrastructure() {\n    log_info \"Deploying infrastructure with Terraform...\"\n    \n    cd \"$TERRAFORM_DIR\"\n    \n    # Initialize Terraform\n    log_info \"Initializing Terraform...\"\n    terraform init\n    \n    # Plan deployment\n    log_info \"Planning Terraform deployment...\"\n    terraform plan -out=tfplan\n    \n    # Apply deployment\n    log_info \"Applying Terraform deployment...\"\n    terraform apply tfplan\n    \n    # Clean up plan file\n    rm -f tfplan\n    \n    log_success \"Infrastructure deployment completed\"\n}\n\n# Validate monitoring setup\nvalidate_monitoring() {\n    log_info \"Validating monitoring setup...\"\n    \n    # Get AWS region\n    AWS_REGION=$(aws configure get region)\n    if [ -z \"$AWS_REGION\" ]; then\n        AWS_REGION=\"us-east-1\"\n        log_warning \"AWS region not set, using default: $AWS_REGION\"\n    fi\n    \n    # Check if CloudWatch dashboard exists\n    DASHBOARD_NAME=$(terraform output -raw dashboard_name 2>/dev/null || echo \"\")\n    if [ -n \"$DASHBOARD_NAME\" ]; then\n        log_info \"Checking CloudWatch dashboard: $DASHBOARD_NAME\"\n        if aws cloudwatch get-dashboard --dashboard-name \"$DASHBOARD_NAME\" --region \"$AWS_REGION\" &> /dev/null; then\n            log_success \"CloudWatch dashboard found: $DASHBOARD_NAME\"\n        else\n            log_warning \"CloudWatch dashboard not found: $DASHBOARD_NAME\"\n        fi\n    fi\n    \n    # Check Lambda functions\n    log_info \"Checking Lambda functions...\"\n    LAMBDA_FUNCTIONS=(\n        \"sparks-signup-trigger\"\n        \"sparks-imageThumbnailGeneration\"\n        \"sparks-express-api\"\n    )\n    \n    for func in \"${LAMBDA_FUNCTIONS[@]}\"; do\n        if aws lambda get-function --function-name \"$func\" --region \"$AWS_REGION\" &> /dev/null; then\n            log_success \"Lambda function found: $func\"\n            \n            # Check if X-Ray tracing is enabled\n            TRACING_CONFIG=$(aws lambda get-function-configuration --function-name \"$func\" --region \"$AWS_REGION\" --query 'TracingConfig.Mode' --output text 2>/dev/null || echo \"\")\n            if [ \"$TRACING_CONFIG\" = \"Active\" ]; then\n                log_success \"X-Ray tracing enabled for: $func\"\n            else\n                log_warning \"X-Ray tracing not enabled for: $func\"\n            fi\n        else\n            log_warning \"Lambda function not found: $func\"\n        fi\n    done\n    \n    # Check CloudWatch log groups\n    log_info \"Checking CloudWatch log groups...\"\n    for func in \"${LAMBDA_FUNCTIONS[@]}\"; do\n        LOG_GROUP=\"/aws/lambda/$func\"\n        if aws logs describe-log-groups --log-group-name-prefix \"$LOG_GROUP\" --region \"$AWS_REGION\" --query 'logGroups[0].logGroupName' --output text 2>/dev/null | grep -q \"$LOG_GROUP\"; then\n            log_success \"Log group found: $LOG_GROUP\"\n        else\n            log_warning \"Log group not found: $LOG_GROUP\"\n        fi\n    done\n}\n\n# Test monitoring functionality\ntest_monitoring() {\n    log_info \"Testing monitoring functionality...\"\n    \n    # Get API Gateway URL\n    API_URL=$(terraform output -raw api_gateway_url 2>/dev/null || echo \"\")\n    if [ -n \"$API_URL\" ]; then\n        log_info \"Testing API endpoint: $API_URL\"\n        \n        # Test health endpoint\n        if curl -s -f \"$API_URL/\" > /dev/null; then\n            log_success \"API health check passed\"\n        else\n            log_warning \"API health check failed\"\n        fi\n        \n        # Test photos endpoint (may require authentication)\n        log_info \"Testing photos endpoint (may require authentication)\"\n        HTTP_STATUS=$(curl -s -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" \"$API_URL/photos\" || echo \"000\")\n        if [ \"$HTTP_STATUS\" = \"200\" ] || [ \"$HTTP_STATUS\" = \"401\" ]; then\n            log_success \"Photos endpoint responding (status: $HTTP_STATUS)\"\n        else\n            log_warning \"Photos endpoint issue (status: $HTTP_STATUS)\"\n        fi\n    else\n        log_warning \"API Gateway URL not found in Terraform outputs\"\n    fi\n    \n    # Wait for metrics to appear (they may take a few minutes)\n    log_info \"Waiting for metrics to appear in CloudWatch (this may take a few minutes)...\"\n    sleep 30\n    \n    # Check for custom metrics\n    AWS_REGION=$(aws configure get region || echo \"us-east-1\")\n    NAMESPACES=(\"Sparks/API\" \"Sparks/Lambda\")\n    \n    for namespace in \"${NAMESPACES[@]}\"; do\n        log_info \"Checking metrics in namespace: $namespace\"\n        METRIC_COUNT=$(aws cloudwatch list-metrics --namespace \"$namespace\" --region \"$AWS_REGION\" --query 'length(Metrics)' --output text 2>/dev/null || echo \"0\")\n        if [ \"$METRIC_COUNT\" -gt 0 ]; then\n            log_success \"Found $METRIC_COUNT metrics in namespace: $namespace\"\n        else\n            log_warning \"No metrics found in namespace: $namespace (may take time to appear)\"\n        fi\n    done\n}\n\n# Generate monitoring report\ngenerate_report() {\n    log_info \"Generating monitoring report...\"\n    \n    REPORT_FILE=\"$PROJECT_ROOT/monitoring-report.txt\"\n    \n    cat > \"$REPORT_FILE\" << EOF\n# Sparks Monitoring Deployment Report\nGenerated: $(date)\n\n## Infrastructure Status\nEOF\n    \n    # Add Terraform outputs\n    cd \"$TERRAFORM_DIR\"\n    echo \"### Terraform Outputs\" >> \"$REPORT_FILE\"\n    terraform output >> \"$REPORT_FILE\" 2>/dev/null || echo \"No Terraform outputs available\" >> \"$REPORT_FILE\"\n    \n    # Add AWS resource information\n    AWS_REGION=$(aws configure get region || echo \"us-east-1\")\n    echo -e \"\\n### AWS Resources\" >> \"$REPORT_FILE\"\n    echo \"Region: $AWS_REGION\" >> \"$REPORT_FILE\"\n    \n    #                 "file_text": "#!/bin/bash\n\n# Sparks PowerTools Monitoring Deployment Script\n# This script deploys the monitoring infrastructure and validates the setup\n\nset -e\n\n# Colors for output\nRED='\\033[0;31m'\nGREEN='\\033[0;32m'\nYELLOW='\\033[1;33m'\nBLUE='\\033[0;34m'\nNC='\\033[0m' # No Color\n\n# Configuration\nPROJECT_ROOT=\"$(cd \"$(dirname \"${BASH_SOURCE[0]}\")/..\" && pwd)\"\nTERRAFORM_DIR=\"$PROJECT_ROOT/terraform\"\nEXPRESS_API_DIR=\"$PROJECT_ROOT/src/express-api\"\n\n# Functions\nlog_info() {\n    echo -e \"${BLUE}[INFO]${NC} $1\"\n}\n\nlog_success() {\n    echo -e \"${GREEN}[SUCCESS]${NC} $1\"\n}\n\nlog_warning() {\n    echo -e \"${YELLOW}[WARNING]${NC} $1\"\n}\n\nlog_error() {\n    echo -e \"${RED}[ERROR]${NC} $1\"\n}\n\n# Check prerequisites\ncheck_prerequisites() {\n    log_info \"Checking prerequisites...\"\n    \n    # Check if AWS CLI is installed\n    if ! command -v aws &> /dev/null; then\n        log_error \"AWS CLI is not installed. Please install it first.\"\n        exit 1\n    fi\n    \n    # Check if Terraform is installed\n    if ! command -v terraform &> /dev/null; then\n        log_error \"Terraform is not installed. Please install it first.\"\n        exit 1\n    fi\n    \n    # Check if Node.js is installed\n    if ! command -v node &> /dev/null; then\n        log_error \"Node.js is not installed. Please install it first.\"\n        exit 1\n    fi\n    \n    # Check AWS credentials\n    if ! aws sts get-caller-identity &> /dev/null; then\n        log_error \"AWS credentials not configured. Please run 'aws configure'.\"\n        exit 1\n    fi\n    \n    log_success \"Prerequisites check passed\"\n}\n\n# Install dependencies\ninstall_dependencies() {\n    log_info \"Installing dependencies...\"\n    \n    # Install Express API dependencies\n    if [ -d \"$EXPRESS_API_DIR\" ]; then\n        log_info \"Installing Express API dependencies...\"\n        cd \"$EXPRESS_API_DIR\"\n        npm install\n        log_success \"Express API dependencies installed\"\n    else\n        log_warning \"Express API directory not found: $EXPRESS_API_DIR\"\n    fi\n    \n    # Install Lambda dependencies (handled by Terraform during deployment)\n    log_info \"Lambda dependencies will be installed during Terraform deployment\"\n}\n\n# Deploy infrastructure\ndeploy_infrastructure() {\n    log_info \"Deploying infrastructure with Terraform...\"\n    \n    cd \"$TERRAFORM_DIR\"\n    \n    # Initialize Terraform\n    log_info \"Initializing Terraform...\"\n    terraform init\n    \n    # Plan deployment\n    log_info \"Planning Terraform deployment...\"\n    terraform plan -out=tfplan\n    \n    # Apply deployment\n    log_info \"Applying Terraform deployment...\"\n    terraform apply tfplan\n    \n    # Clean up plan file\n    rm -f tfplan\n    \n    log_success \"Infrastructure deployment completed\"\n}\n\n# Validate monitoring setup\nvalidate_monitoring() {\n    log_info \"Validating monitoring setup...\"\n    \n    # Get AWS region\n    AWS_REGION=$(aws configure get region)\n    if [ -z \"$AWS_REGION\" ]; then\n        AWS_REGION=\"us-east-1\"\n        log_warning \"AWS region not set, using default: $AWS_REGION\"\n    fi\n    \n    # Check if CloudWatch dashboard exists\n    DASHBOARD_NAME=$(terraform output -raw dashboard_name 2>/dev/null || echo \"\")\n    if [ -n \"$DASHBOARD_NAME\" ]; then\n        log_info \"Checking CloudWatch dashboard: $DASHBOARD_NAME\"\n        if aws cloudwatch get-dashboard --dashboard-name \"$DASHBOARD_NAME\" --region \"$AWS_REGION\" &> /dev/null; then\n            log_success \"CloudWatch dashboard found: $DASHBOARD_NAME\"\n        else\n            log_warning \"CloudWatch dashboard not found: $DASHBOARD_NAME\"\n        fi\n    fi\n    \n    # Check Lambda functions\n    log_info \"Checking Lambda functions...\"\n    LAMBDA_FUNCTIONS=(\n        \"sparks-signup-trigger\"\n        \"sparks-imageThumbnailGeneration\"\n        \"sparks-express-api\"\n    )\n    \n    for func in \"${LAMBDA_FUNCTIONS[@]}\"; do\n        if aws lambda get-function --function-name \"$func\" --region \"$AWS_REGION\" &> /dev/null; then\n            log_success \"Lambda function found: $func\"\n            \n            # Check if X-Ray tracing is enabled\n            TRACING_CONFIG=$(aws lambda get-function-configuration --function-name \"$func\" --region \"$AWS_REGION\" --query 'TracingConfig.Mode' --output text 2>/dev/null || echo \"\")\n            if [ \"$TRACING_CONFIG\" = \"Active\" ]; then\n                log_success \"X-Ray tracing enabled for: $func\"\n            else\n                log_warning \"X-Ray tracing not enabled for: $func\"\n            fi\n        else\n            log_warning \"Lambda function not found: $func\"\n        fi\n    done\n    \n    # Check CloudWatch log groups\n    log_info \"Checking CloudWatch log groups...\"\n    for func in \"${LAMBDA_FUNCTIONS[@]}\"; do\n        LOG_GROUP=\"/aws/lambda/$func\"\n        if aws logs describe-log-groups --log-group-name-prefix \"$LOG_GROUP\" --region \"$AWS_REGION\" --query 'logGroups[0].logGroupName' --output text 2>/dev/null | grep -q \"$LOG_GROUP\"; then\n            log_success \"Log group found: $LOG_GROUP\"\n        else\n            log_warning \"Log group not found: $LOG_GROUP\"\n        fi\n    done\n}\n\n# Test monitoring functionality\ntest_monitoring() {\n    log_info \"Testing monitoring functionality...\"\n    \n    # Get API Gateway URL\n    API_URL=$(terraform output -raw api_gateway_url 2>/dev/null || echo \"\")\n    if [ -n \"$API_URL\" ]; then\n        log_info \"Testing API endpoint: $API_URL\"\n        \n        # Test health endpoint\n        if curl -s -f \"$API_URL/\" > /dev/null; then\n            log_success \"API health check passed\"\n        else\n            log_warning \"API health check failed\"\n        fi\n        \n        # Test photos endpoint (may require authentication)\n        log_info \"Testing photos endpoint (may require authentication)\"\n        HTTP_STATUS=$(curl -s -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" \"$API_URL/photos\" || echo \"000\")\n        if [ \"$HTTP_STATUS\" = \"200\" ] || [ \"$HTTP_STATUS\" = \"401\" ]; then\n            log_success \"Photos endpoint responding (status: $HTTP_STATUS)\"\n        else\n            log_warning \"Photos endpoint issue (status: $HTTP_STATUS)\"\n        fi\n    else\n        log_warning \"API Gateway URL not found in Terraform outputs\"\n    fi\n    \n    # Wait for metrics to appear (they may take a few minutes)\n    log_info \"Waiting for metrics to appear in CloudWatch (this may take a few minutes)...\"\n    sleep 30\n    \n    # Check for custom metrics\n    AWS_REGION=$(aws configure get region || echo \"us-east-1\")\n    NAMESPACES=(\"Sparks/API\" \"Sparks/Lambda\")\n    \n    for namespace in \"${NAMESPACES[@]}\"; do\n        log_info \"Checking metrics in namespace: $namespace\"\n        METRIC_COUNT=$(aws cloudwatch list-metrics --namespace \"$namespace\" --region \"$AWS_REGION\" --query 'length(Metrics)' --output text 2>/dev/null || echo \"0\")\n        if [ \"$METRIC_COUNT\" -gt 0 ]; then\n            log_success \"Found $METRIC_COUNT metrics in namespace: $namespace\"\n        else\n            log_warning \"No metrics found in namespace: $namespace (may take time to appear)\"\n        fi\n    done\n}\n\n# Generate monitoring report\ngenerate_report() {\n    log_info \"Generating monitoring report...\"\n    \n    REPORT_FILE=\"$PROJECT_ROOT/monitoring-report.txt\"\n    \n    cat > \"$REPORT_FILE\" << EOF\n# Sparks Monitoring Deployment Report\nGenerated: $(date)\n\n## Infrastructure Status\nEOF\n    \n    # Add Terraform outputs\n    cd \"$TERRAFORM_DIR\"\n    echo \"### Terraform Outputs\" >> \"$REPORT_FILE\"\n    terraform output >> \"$REPORT_FILE\" 2>/dev/null || echo \"No Terraform outputs available\" >> \"$REPORT_FILE\"\n    \n    # Add AWS resource information\n    AWS_REGION=$(aws configure get region || echo \"us-east-1\")\n    echo -e \"\\n### AWS Resources\" >> \"$REPORT_FILE\"\n    echo \"Region: $AWS_REGION\" >> \"$REPORT_FILE\"\n    \n    # Lambda functions\n    echo -e \"\\n#### Lambda Functions\" >> \"$REPORT_FILE\"\n    aws lambda list-functions --region \"$AWS_REGION\" --query 'Functions[?starts_with(FunctionName, `sparks`)].{Name:FunctionName,Runtime:Runtime,Timeout:Timeout,Memory:MemorySize}' --output table >> \"$REPORT_FILE\" 2>/dev/null || echo \"Error retrieving Lambda functions\" >> \"$REPORT_FILE\"\n    \n    # CloudWatch dashboards\n    echo -e \"\\n#### CloudWatch Dashboards\" >> \"$REPORT_FILE\"\n    aws cloudwatch list-dashboards --region \"$AWS_REGION\" --query 'DashboardEntries[?contains(DashboardName, `sparks`)].{Name:DashboardName,LastModified:LastModified}' --output table >> \"$REPORT_FILE\" 2>/dev/null || echo \"Error retrieving dashboards\" >> \"$REPORT_FILE\"\n    \n    log_success \"Monitoring report generated: $REPORT_FILE\"\n}\n\n# Main execution\nmain() {\n    log_info \"Starting Sparks PowerTools Monitoring Deployment\"\n    log_info \"Project root: $PROJECT_ROOT\"\n    \n    # Parse command line arguments\n    SKIP_DEPLOY=false\n    SKIP_TEST=false\n    \n    while [[ $# -gt 0 ]]; do\n        case $1 in\n            --skip-deploy)\n                SKIP_DEPLOY=true\n                shift\n                ;;\n            --skip-test)\n                SKIP_TEST=true\n                shift\n                ;;\n            --help)\n                echo \"Usage: $0 [--skip-deploy] [--skip-test] [--help]\"\n                echo \"  --skip-deploy  Skip infrastructure deployment\"\n                echo \"  --skip-test    Skip monitoring tests\"\n                echo \"  --help         Show this help message\"\n                exit 0\n                ;;\n            *)\n                log_error \"Unknown option: $1\"\n                exit 1\n                ;;\n        esac\n    done\n    \n    # Execute deployment steps\n    check_prerequisites\n    install_dependencies\n    \n    if [ \"$SKIP_DEPLOY\" = false ]; then\n        deploy_infrastructure\n    else\n        log_info \"Skipping infrastructure deployment\"\n    fi\n    \n    validate_monitoring\n    \n    if [ \"$SKIP_TEST\" = false ]; then\n        test_monitoring\n    else\n        log_info \"Skipping monitoring tests\"\n    fi\n    \n    generate_report\n    \n    log_success \"Sparks PowerTools Monitoring deployment completed!\"\n    log_info \"Check the monitoring report: $PROJECT_ROOT/monitoring-report.txt\"\n    log_info \"Access your CloudWatch dashboard in the AWS Console\"\n}\n\n# Run main function\nmain \"$@\"",

encodeURIComponent(JSON.stringify(LastEvaluatedKey)) : null,\n    });\n  } catch (err) {\n    console.error('Error getting users:', err);\n    res.status(500).json({ error: 'Could not retrieve users' });\n  }\n});\n\n// GET /users/:email - Get user info\nrouter.get('/:email', async (req, res) => {\n  const { email } = req.params;\n\n  const params = {\n    TableName: TABLE_NAME,\n    Key: {\n      PK: email,\n      SK: email\n    }\n  };\n\n  try {\n    const command = new GetCommand(params);\n    const { Item } = await docClient.send(command);\n\n    if (!Item) {\n      return res.status(404).json({ error: 'User not found' });\n    }\n\n    res.json(Item);\n  } catch (err) {\n    console.error(`Error getting user info for ${email}:`, err);\n    res.status(500).json({ error: 'Could not retrieve user info' });\n  }\n});\n\n\n// GET /users/:email/photos - Get photos uploaded by a specific user with pagination\nrouter.get('/:email/photos', async (req, res) => {\n  const { email } = req.params;\n  const { lastEvaluatedKey } = req.query;\n\n  const params = {\n    TableName: TABLE_NAME,\n    IndexName: 'uploadedBy-PK-index',\n    KeyConditionExpression: 'uploadedBy = :email',\n    ExpressionAttributeValues: {\n      ':email': email,\n    },\n    Limit: 100,\n  };\n\n  if (lastEvaluatedKey) {\n    params.ExclusiveStartKey = JSON.parse(decodeURIComponent(lastEvaluatedKey));\n  }\n\n  try {\n    const command = new QueryCommand(params);\n    const { Items, LastEvaluatedKey } = await docClient.send(command);\n\n    // Generate signed URLs for all images\n    const itemsWithSignedUrls = await Promise.all(Items.map(async item => {\n      // Generate signed URLs for main image and thumbnail\n      const imageUrl = CLOUDFRONT_DOMAIN + item.s3Key;\n      const thumbnailUrl = item.thumbnailFileName ?                   {
                    "Text": "const express = require('express');\nconst router = express.Router();\nconst { S3Client, PutObjectCommand } = require(\"@aws-sdk/client-s3\");\nconst { getSignedUrl } = require(\"@aws-sdk/s3-request-presigner\");\nconst KSUID = require('ksuid');\nconst { DynamoDBClient } = require(\"@aws-sdk/client-dynamodb\");\nconst { DynamoDBDocumentClient, GetCommand, QueryCommand, PutCommand, UpdateCommand } = require(\"@aws-sdk/lib-dynamodb\");\nconst authMiddleware = require('../middleware/auth');\n\nconst s3Client = new S3Client({});\nconst dynamoClient = new DynamoDBClient({});\nconst docClient = DynamoDBDocumentClient.from(dynamoClient);\n\nconst TABLE_NAME = process.env.DDB_TABLE_NAME;\nconst BUCKET_NAME = process.env.S3_BUCKET_NAME;\n\n// Apply auth middleware to all routes in this file\nrouter.use(authMiddleware);\n\n// GET / - Get a pre-signed S3 URL for uploading a new photo\nrouter.get('/', async (req, res) => {\n  const { email } = req.user;\n\n  try {\n    // Check user's upload limit from DEFAULT_LIMIT entity\n    const limitParams = {\n      TableName: TABLE_NAME,\n      Key: {\n        PK: `LIMIT#${email}`,\n        SK: email\n      }\n    };\n    const limitCommand = new GetCommand(limitParams);\n    const { Item: limitItem } = await docClient.send(limitCommand);\n\n    if (!limitItem || typeof limitItem.limit !== 'number') {\n      return res.status(403).json({ error: 'Upload limit not set for user' });\n    }\n    if (limitItem.limit <= 0) {\n      return res.status(403).json({ error: 'Upload limit reached' });\n    }\n\n    // Generate a unique, time-ordered key for the new image using KSUID\n    const imageId = KSUID.randomSync().string;\n    const key = `originals/${imageId}.jpg`;\n\n    // Create the pre-signed URL\n    const command = new PutObjectCommand({\n      Bucket: BUCKET_NAME,\n      Key: key,\n      ContentType: 'image/jpeg',\n    });\n\n    const signedUrl = await getSignedUrl(s3Client, command, { expiresIn: 3600 });\n\n    res.json({\n      uploadUrl: signedUrl,\n      imageId: imageId,\n      key: key,\n    });\n  } catch (err) {\n    console.error(`Error generating upload URL for user ${email}:`, err);\n    res.status(500).json({ error: 'Could not generate upload URL' });\n  }\n});\n\n// POST /complete - Create a record in DynamoDB after a successful upload\nrouter.post('/complete', async (req, res) => {\n  const { email } = req.user;\n  const { imageId, key, description, tags } = req.body;\n\n  if (!imageId || !key) {\n    return res.status(400).json({ error: 'imageId and key are required.' });\n  }\n\n  const timestamp = new Date().toISOString();\n\n  const params = {\n    TableName: TABLE_NAME,\n    Item: {\n      PK: imageId,\n      SK: `UPLOADED_BY#${email}`,\n      entityType: 'IMAGE',\n      assetType: 'IMAGE',\n      uploadedBy: email,\n      imageId: imageId,\n      s3Key: key,\n      thumbnailFileName: \"\",\n      description: description || '',\n      tags: tags || [],\n      persons: [],\n      uploaded_datetime: timestamp,\n    },\n  };\n\n  try {\n    // Insert photo record\n    const command = new PutCommand(params);\n    await docClient.send(command);\n\n    // Decrement DEFAULT_LIMIT for user\n    const updateLimitParams = {\n      TableName: TABLE_NAME,\n      Key: {\n        PK: `LIMIT#${email}`,\n        SK: email\n      },\n      UpdateExpression: 'SET #limit = #limit - :dec',\n      ExpressionAttributeNames: { '#limit': 'limit' },\n      ExpressionAttributeValues: { ':dec': 1, ':zero': 0 },\n      ConditionExpression: '#limit > :zero',\n      ReturnValues: 'ALL_NEW'\n    };\n    try {\n      await docClient.send(new UpdateCommand(updateLimitParams));\n    } catch (limitErr) {\n      // If limit update fails, log but do not block photo creation response\n      console.error(`Error decrementing upload limit for user ${email}:`, limitErr);\n    }\n\n    res.status(201).json(params.Item);\n  } catch (err) {\n    console.error(`Error creating photo record for user ${email}:`, err);\n    res.status(500).json({ error: 'Could not create photo record.' });\n  }\n});\n\nmodule.exports = router;"

                    "Text": "const express = require('express');\nconst router = express.Router();\nconst { v4: uuidv4 } = require('uuid');\nconst path = require('path');\nconst { DynamoDBClient } = require(\"@aws-sdk/client-dynamodb\");\nconst {\n  DynamoDBDocumentClient,\n  GetCommand,\n  QueryCommand,\n  UpdateCommand,\n  PutCommand,\n  TransactWriteCommand\n} = process.env.DDB_TABLE_NAME;\nconst CLOUDFRONT_DOMAIN = process.env.CLOUDFRONT_DOMAIN || '';\nconst S3_BUCKET = process.env.S3_BUCKET_NAME;\nconst FACE_RECOGNITION_QUEUE_URL = process.env.FACE_RECOGNITION_QUEUE_URL;\n\n// URL expiration time in seconds (24 hours)\nconst URL_EXPIRATION = 24 * 60 * 60;\n\n// Apply the auth middleware to all routes in this file\nrouter.use(authMiddleware);\n\n// GET /me/photos - Get all photos uploaded by the current user with pagination\nrouter.get('/photos', async (req, res) => {\n  const { email } = req.user;\n  const { lastEvaluatedKey } = req.query;\n\n  const params = {\n    TableName: TABLE_NAME,\n    IndexName: 'uploadedBy-PK-index',\n    KeyConditionExpression: 'uploadedBy = :email',\n    ExpressionAttributeValues: {\n      ':email': email,\n    },\n    Limit: 100,\n  };\n\n  if (lastEvaluatedKey) {\n    params.ExclusiveStartKey = JSON.parse(decodeURIComponent(lastEvaluatedKey));\n  }\n\n  try {\n    const command = new QueryCommand(params);\n    const { Items, LastEvaluatedKey } = await docClient.send(command);\n\n    // Generate signed URLs for all image variants\n    const itemsWithSignedUrls = await Promise.all(Items.map(async item => {\n      // Create a deep copy of the item\n      const processedItem = { ...item };\n\n      // Handle original image URL\n      if (item.s3Key) {\n        const originalUrl = CLOUDFRONT_DOMAIN + item.s3Key;\n        processedItem.s3Key = await getSignedUrl(originalUrl, { expireTime: URL_EXPIRATION });\n      }\n\n      // Handle thumbnail URL\n      if (item.thumbnailFileName) {\n        const thumbnailUrl = CLOUDFRONT_DOMAIN + item.thumbnailFileName;\n        processedItem.thumbnailFileName = await getSignedUrl(thumbnailUrl, { expireTime: URL_EXPIRATION });\n      }\n\n      // Handle processed image variants (large, medium)\n      if (item.images) {\n        processedItem.images = { ...item.images };\n\n        if (item.images.large) {\n          const largeUrl = CLOUDFRONT_DOMAIN + item.images.large;\n          processedItem.images.large = await getSignedUrl(largeUrl, { expireTime: URL_EXPIRATION });\n        }\n\n        if (item.images.medium) {\n          const mediumUrl = CLOUDFRONT_DOMAIN + item.images.medium;\n          processedItem.images.medium = await getSignedUrl(mediumUrl, { expireTime: URL_EXPIRATION });\n        }\n      }\n\n      return processedItem;\n    }));\n\n    res.json({\n      items: itemsWithSignedUrls,\n      lastEvaluatedKey: LastEvaluatedKey ? encodeURIComponent(JSON.stringify(LastEvaluatedKey)) : null,\n    });\n  } catch (err) {\n    console.error(`Error getting photos for user ${email}:`, err);\n    res.status(500).json({ error: 'Could not retrieve photos' });\n  }\n});\n\n// GET /me/limit - Get the current user's upload limit\nrouter.get('/limit', async (req, res) => {\n  const { email } = req.user;\n\n  const params = {\n    TableName: TABLE_NAME,\n    Key: {\n      PK: `USER#${email}`,\n      SK: `USER#${email}`\n    }\n  };\n\n  try {\n    const command = new GetCommand(params);\n    const { Item } = await docClient.send(command);\n\n    if (!Item) {\n      return res.status(404).json({ error: 'User not found' });\n    }\n\n    res.json({\n      uploadLimit: Item.uploadLimit || 100\n    });\n  } catch (err) {\n    console.error(`Error getting upload limit for user ${email}:`, err);\n    res.status(500).json({ error: 'Could not retrieve upload limit' });\n  }\n});\n\n// PUT /me/limit - Set the current user's upload limit (for admin use in the future)\nrouter.put('/limit', async (req, res) => {\n  const { email } = req.user;\n  const { limit } = req.body;\n\n  if (limit === undefined || typeof limit !== 'number' || limit < 0) {\n    return res.status(400).json({ error: 'Invalid limit value' });\n  }\n\n  const params = {\n    TableName: TABLE_NAME,\n    Key: {\n      PK: `USER#${email}`,\n      SK: `USER#${email}`\n    },\n    UpdateExpression: 'SET uploadLimit = :limit',\n    ExpressionAttributeValues: {\n      ':limit': limit\n    },\n    ReturnValues: 'ALL_NEW'\n  };\n\n  try {\n    const command = new UpdateCommand(params);\n    const { Attributes } = await docClient.send(command);\n\n    res.json({\n      uploadLimit: Attributes.uploadLimit\n    });\n  } catch (err) {\n    console.error(`Error updating upload limit for user ${email}:`, err);\n    res.status(500).json({ error: 'Could not update upload limit' });\n  }\n});\n\n// GET /me/profile - Get the current user's profile information including personId if set\nrouter.get('/profile', async (req, res) => {\n  const { email } = req.user;\n\n  const params = {\n    TableName: TABLE_NAME,\n    Key: {\n      PK: `${email}`,\n      SK: `${email}`\n    }\n  };\n\n  try {\n    const command = new GetCommand(params);\n    const { Item } = await docClient.send(command);\n\n    if (!Item) {\n      return res.status(404).json({ error: 'User not found' });\n    }\n\n    console.log(\"user profile\", Item)\n\n    if (Item.profilePicture) {\n      const profilePicUrl = CLOUDFRONT_DOMAIN + async (req, res) => {\n  const { email } = req.user;\n  const { key } = req.body;\n\n  if (!key) {\n    return res.status(400).json({ error: 'key is required' });\n  }\n\n  try {\n    // 1. First check if the user record exists\n    const getUserParams = {\n      TableName: TABLE_NAME,\n      Key: {\n        PK: email,\n        SK: email\n      }\n    };\n\n    const getCommand = new GetCommand(getUserParams);\n    const { Item: userItem } = await docClient.send(getCommand);\n\n    if (!userItem) {\n      // User doesn't exist, create a new user record\n      console.log(`User ${email} not found, creating new user record`);\n\n      // Extract preferred username from auth token\n      const preferredUsername = req.user['preferred_username'] || req.user['cognito:username'] || email;\n      console.log(`Using preferred username: ${preferredUsername}`);\n\n      const userInsertParam = {\n        TableName: TABLE_NAME,\n        Item: {\n          PK: email,\n          SK: email,\n          entityType: \"USER\",\n          username: preferredUsername,\n          email: email,\n          profilePicture: key,\n          updatedAt: new Date().toISOString(),\n          createdAt: new Date().toISOString()\n        }\n      };\n\n      const putCommand = new PutCommand(userInsertParam);\n      await docClient.send(putCommand);\n    } else {\n      // User exists, update the profile picture\n      const updateUserParams = {\n        TableName: TABLE_NAME,\n        Key: {\n          PK: email,\n          SK: email\n        },\n        UpdateExpression: 'SET profilePicture = :profilePic, updatedAt = :updatedAt, entityType = :entityType, email = :email',\n        ExpressionAttributeValues: {\n          ':profilePic': key,\n          ':updatedAt': new Date().toISOString(),\n          ':entityType': 'USER',\n          ':email': email\n        },\n        ReturnValues: 'ALL_NEW'\n      };\n\n      const updateCommand = new UpdateCommand(updateUserParams);\n      await docClient.send(updateCommand);\n    }\n\n    // 2. Send message to face recognition SQS queue\n    if (FACE_RECOGNITION_QUEUE_URL) {\n      try {\n        const messagePayload = {\n          bucketName: S3_BUCKET,\n          objectKey: key,\n          isProfilePicture: true,\n          userEmail: email\n        };\n\n        const sendParams = {\n          QueueUrl: FACE_RECOGNITION_QUEUE_URL,\n          MessageBody: JSON.stringify(messagePayload),\n          MessageGroupId: 'profile-picture',\n          MessageDeduplicationId: key,\n          MessageAttributes: {\n            'MessageType': {\n              DataType: 'String',\n              StringValue: 'PROFILE_PICTURE'\n            }\n          }\n        };\n\n        const sendCommand = new SendMessageCommand(sendParams);\n        await sqsClient.send(sendCommand);\n\n        console.log(`Message sent to face recognition queue for profile picture: ${key}`);\n      } catch (sqsError) {\n        console.error('Error sending message to face recognition queue:', sqsError);\n        // Don't fail the request if SQS message sending fails\n      }\n    }\n\n    // 3. Generate signed URL for the profile picture\n\n    const profilePicUrl = CLOUDFRONT_DOMAIN + key;\n    const signedUrl = await getSignedUrl(profilePicUrl, { expireTime: URL_EXPIRATION });\n\n    return res.json({\n      profilePictureUrl: signedUrl,\n      message: 'Profile picture uploaded successfully. First get the user's personId\n    const getUserParams = {\n      TableName: TABLE_NAME,\n      Key: {\n        PK: email,\n        SK: email\n      }\n    };\n\n    const userCommand = new GetCommand(getUserParams);\n    const { Item: userItem } = await docClient.send(userCommand);\n\n    if (!userItem || !userItem.personId) {\n      return res.json({\n        items: [],\n        lastEvaluatedKey: null,\n        message: 'No profile picture uploaded yet.                     "Text": "const express = require('express');\nconst router = express.Router();\nconst { DynamoDBClient } = require(\"@aws-sdk/client-dynamodb\");\nconst { DynamoDBDocumentClient, PutCommand } = require(\"@aws-sdk/lib-dynamodb\");\nconst KSUID = require('ksuid');\n\nconst client = new DynamoDBClient({});\nconst docClient = DynamoDBDocumentClient.from(client);\n\nconst TABLE_NAME = process.env.DDB_TABLE_NAME;\n\n// Helper function to get the current user's email from the Cognito JWT token\nfunction getUserEmailFromToken(req) {\n  // In a real implementation, this would extract the email from the JWT token\n  // For now, we'll use the 'x-user-email' header for testing\n  return req.headers['x-user-email'] || 'unknown@example.com';\n}\n\n// POST /events - Log a web event\nrouter.post('/', async (req, res) => {\n  const email = getUserEmailFromToken(req);\n  const { eventType, eventData } = req.body;\n  \n  if (!eventType) {\n    return res.status(400).json({ error: 'Event type is required' });\n  }\n\n  const timestamp = new Date().toISOString();\n  const eventId = KSUID.randomSync().string;\n\n  const params = {\n    TableName: TABLE_NAME,\n    Item: {\n      PK: `EVENT#${eventId}`,\n      SK: `EVENT#${timestamp}`,\n      entityType: 'EVENT',\n      eventType: eventType,\n      eventData: eventData || {},\n      email: email,\n      createdAt: timestamp\n    }\n  };\n\n  try {\n    const command = new PutCommand(params);\n    await docClient.send(command);\n    \n    res.status(201).json({\n      eventId: eventId,\n      timestamp: timestamp\n    });\n  } catch (err) {\n    console.error(`Error logging event for user ${email}:`, err);\n    res.status(500).json({ error: 'Could not log event' });\n  }\n});\n\nmodule.exports = router;"

                "file_text": "# Express API PowerTools Integration - Complete Implementation Summary\n\nThis document provides a comprehensive overview of the PowerTools integration across all Express API routes in the Sparks photo-sharing platform.\n\n## Overview\n\nAll Express API routes have been updated with comprehensive AWS PowerTools integration following the best practices established in the `photos.js` route. Each route now includes:\n\n- **Distributed Tracing** with AWS X-Ray\n- **Structured Logging** with contextual information\n- **Custom Metrics** for business and performance monitoring\n- **Error Handling** with proper correlation and metadata\n\n## Completed Routes\n\n### 1. Photos Route (`routes/photos.js`)\n**Endpoints:**\n- `GET /photos` - Get all photos with pagination\n- `GET /photos/:id` - Get specific photo by ID\n- `GET /photos/:id/persons` - Get persons detected in a photo\n\n**Key Features:**\n- Comprehensive tracing with subsegments for each operation\n- Custom metrics for photos queried, signed URLs generated, errors\n- Detailed logging with photo metadata and performance metrics\n- Error correlation across DynamoDB queries and CloudFront operations\n\n**Metrics Generated:**\n- `PhotosQueried`, `PhotoRetrieved`, `PhotoPersonsRetrieved`\n- `SignedUrlsGenerated`, `DynamoDBQueries`\n- `PhotosQueryErrors`, `PhotoRetrievalErrors`, `PhotoPersonsErrors`\n\n### 2. Users Route (`routes/users.js`)\n**Endpoints:**\n- `GET /users` - Get all users with pagination\n- `GET /users/:email` - Get user info by email\n- `GET /users/:email/photos` - Get photos uploaded by specific user\n\n**Key Features:**\n- User-centric tracing and logging\n- Metrics for user queries and photo retrieval\n- Signed URL generation tracking for user photos\n- Performance monitoring for user-specific operations\n\n**Metrics Generated:**\n- `UsersQueried`, `UserRetrieved`, `UserPhotosQueried`\n- `SignedUrlsGenerated`, `DynamoDBQueries`\n- `UsersQueryErrors`, `UserRetrievalErrors`, `UserPhotosQueryErrors`\n\n### 3. Persons Route (`routes/persons.js`)\n**Endpoints:**\n- `GET /persons` - Get all unique people with pagination\n- `GET /persons/:personId` - Get person info by ID\n- `GET /persons/:personId/photos` - Get photos where person is tagged\n- `PUT /persons/:personId` - Update person's name\n\n**Key Features:**\n- Face recognition and tagging operation tracking\n- Person management metrics and logging\n- Photo tagging correlation tracking\n- Name update operations with validation\n\n**Metrics Generated:**\n- `PersonsQueried`, `PersonRetrieved`, `PersonPhotosQueried`\n- `PersonNameUpdated`, `DynamoDBUpdates`\n- `PersonsQueryErrors`, `PersonRetrievalErrors`, `PersonUpdateErrors`\n\n### 4. Upload Route (`routes/upload.js`)\n**Endpoints:**\n- `GET /upload` - Get pre-signed S3 URL for uploading\n- `POST /upload/complete` - Complete upload and create DynamoDB record\n\n**Key Features:**\n- Upload limit validation and tracking\n- Pre-signed URL generation monitoring\n- Upload completion workflow tracing\n- User limit management with metrics\n\n**Metrics Generated:**\n- `PresignedUrlsGenerated`, `UploadsCompleted`, `PhotoRecordsCreated`\n- `UserLimitsDecremented`, `UploadsWithDescription`, `UploadsWithTags`\n- `PresignedUrlErrors`, `UploadCompletionErrors`, `LimitDecrementErrors`\n\n### 5. Me Route (`routes/me.js`)\n**Endpoints:**\n- `GET /me/photos` - Get current user's photos\n- `GET /me/limit` - Get current user's upload limit\n- `PUT /me/limit` - Update current user's upload limit\n- `GET /me/profile` - Get current user's profile\n- `GET /me/profile-picture-upload` - Get profile picture upload URL\n- `POST /me/profile-picture/complete` - Complete profile picture upload\n- `GET /me/photos-with-me` - Get photos where current user is detected\n\n**Key Features:**\n- Comprehensive user profile management\n- Face recognition integration tracking\n- Profile picture upload workflow monitoring\n- Personal photo discovery with face detection\n\n**Metrics Generated:**\n- `MyPhotosQueried`, `UserLimitRetrieved`, `UserLimitUpdated`\n- `ProfilePictureUploadUrlsGenerated`, `ProfilePictureUploadsCompleted`\n- `PhotosWithMeQueried`, `FaceRecognitionMessagesQueued`\n- `UserProfileRetrieved`, `UserRecordsCreated`, `UserRecordsUpdated`\n\n### 6. Events Route (`routes/events.js`)\n**Endpoints:**\n- `POST /events` - Log web events\n\n**Key Features:**\n- Web analytics and user behavior tracking\n- Event type categorization and metrics\n- Event data size and complexity monitoring\n- User activity correlation\n\n**Metrics Generated:**\n- `EventsLogged`, `EventsWithData`, `EventDataSize`\n- `{EventType}Events` (dynamic metrics per event type)\n- `EventLoggingErrors`, `EventValidationErrors`\n\n### 7. Livestream Route (`routes/livestream.js`)\n**Endpoints:**\n- `GET /livestream` - Get current livestream status\n\n**Key Features:**\n- Livestream availability checking\n- Active vs expired livestream tracking\n- Viewer request monitoring\n- Livestream performance metrics\n\n**Metrics Generated:**\n- `LivestreamQueries`, `ActiveLivestreamsFound`, `ExpiredLivestreamsFound`\n- `LivestreamViewRequests`, `InactiveLivestreamRequests`\n- `LivestreamQueryErrors`, `NoLivestreamsFound`\n\n### 8. Proxy Route (`routes/proxy.js`)\n**Endpoints:**\n- `GET /proxy/image` - Proxy image downloads from CloudFront\n\n**Key Features:**\n- Image download proxying with performance tracking\n- CloudFront integration monitoring\n- Data transfer metrics and timing\n- Security validation for URLs\n\n**Metrics Generated:**\n- `ImageDownloadsProxied`, `ProxyDownloadTime`, `ProxyDataTransferred`\n- `ProxyStreamingCompleted`, `ProxyDownloadErrors`\n- `ProxyTimeoutErrors`, `ProxyHttpErrors`, `ProxyNetworkErrors`\n\n## Common PowerTools Patterns\n\n### 1. Route Segment Creation\n```javascript\nconst subsegment = createRouteSegment('routeName', 'operationName');\n```\n\n### 2. Structured Logging\n```javascript\nlogger.info('Operation description', {\n  operation: 'operationName',\n  userEmail: email,\n  additionalContext: value\n});\n```\n\n### 3. Custom Metrics\n```javascript\naddCustomMetric('MetricName', value, MetricUnit.Count);\naddCustomMetric('MetricName', value, MetricUnit.Count, { dimension: 'value' });\n```\n\n### 4.                 "file_text": "# PowerTools Deployment Checklist\n\nThis checklist ensures proper deployment and validation of the AWS PowerTools monitoring implementation across the Sparks platform.\n\n## Pre-Deployment Checklist\n\n###  Code Implementation\n- [ ] All Express API routes updated with PowerTools integration\n- [ ] Lambda functions updated with PowerTools decorators\n- [ ] PowerTools utility module created (`utils/powertools.js`)\n- [ ] Package.json files updated with PowerTools dependencies\n- [ ] Terraform configuration updated with environment variables\n\n###  Dependencies Verification\n- [ ] Express API dependencies installed: `@aws-lambda-powertools/logger`, `@aws-lambda-powertools/tracer`, `@aws-lambda-powertools/metrics`\n- [ ] Lambda function dependencies configured in package.json files\n- [ ] X-Ray SDK packages installed: `aws-xray-sdk-core`, `aws-xray-sdk-express`\n\n###  Infrastructure Configuration\n- [ ] Terraform Lambda module updated with PowerTools environment variables\n- [ ] CloudWatch dashboard configuration updated\n- [ ] CloudWatch alarms configured for critical metrics\n- [ ] X-Ray tracing enabled for all Lambda functions\n\n## Deployment Steps\n\n### 1. Install Dependencies\n```bash\n# Express API\ncd src/express-api/\nnpm install\n\n# Verify PowerTools packages\nnpm list @aws-lambda-powertools/logger\nnpm list @aws-lambda-powertools/tracer\nnpm list @aws-lambda-powertools/metrics\n```\n\n### 2. Deploy Infrastructure\n```bash\n# Run deployment script\n./scripts/deploy-monitoring.sh\n\n# Or manual deployment\ncd terraform/\nterraform init\nterraform plan\nterraform apply\n```\n\n### 3. Verify Environment Variables\nCheck that all Lambda functions have the following environment variables:\n- [ ] `POWERTOOLS_SERVICE_NAME`\n- [ ] `POWERTOOLS_LOG_LEVEL`\n- [ ] `POWERTOOLS_LOGGER_LOG_EVENT`\n- [ ] `POWERTOOLS_TRACER_CAPTURE_RESPONSE`\n- [ ] `POWERTOOLS_TRACER_CAPTURE_ERROR`\n- [ ] `POWERTOOLS_METRICS_NAMESPACE`\n- [ ] `_X_AMZN_TRACE_ID`\n\n## Post-Deployment Validation\n\n###  Functional Testing\n\n#### Express API Routes\nTest each route and verify functionality:\n- [ ] `GET /` - Health check\n- [ ] `GET /photos` - Photo listing\n- [ ] `GET /photos/:id` - Photo details\n- [ ] `GET /users` - User listing\n- [ ] `GET /users/:email` - User details\n- [ ] `GET /persons` - Person listing\n- [ ] `GET /upload` - Upload URL generation\n- [ ] `POST /upload/complete` - Upload completion\n- [ ] `GET /me/profile` - User profile\n- [ ] `POST /events` - Event logging\n- [ ] `GET /livestream` - Livestream status\n- [ ] `GET /proxy/image` - Image proxy\n\n#### Lambda Functions\nTest Lambda function invocations:\n- [ ] Image thumbnail generation\n- [ ] Signup trigger\n- [ ] Face recognition (if applicable)\n\n###  Monitoring Validation\n\n#### CloudWatch Logs\nVerify structured logging:\n- [ ] Express API logs contain PowerTools structured format\n- [ ] Lambda function logs show PowerTools decorators working\n- [ ] Log entries include correlation IDs and context\n- [ ] Error logs include stack traces and metadata\n\n#### X-Ray Traces\nVerify distributed tracing:\n- [ ] API Gateway requests show in X-Ray console\n- [ ] Lambda function traces appear with subsegments\n- [ ] DynamoDB operations traced\n- [ ] S3 operations traced\n- [ ] Error traces include exception details\n\n#### CloudWatch Metrics\nVerify custom metrics:\n- [ ] `Sparks/API` namespace contains API metrics\n- [ ] `Sparks/Lambda` namespace contains Lambda metrics\n- [ ] Business metrics appear (PhotosQueried, UsersRetrieved, etc.)\n- [ ] Error metrics appear (PhotosQueryErrors, etc.)\n- [ ] Performance metrics appear (ResponseTime, etc.)\n\n#### CloudWatch Dashboard\nVerify dashboard widgets:\n- [ ] API Gateway metrics widget shows data\n- [ ] Lambda function metrics widget shows data\n- [ ] Image processing metrics widget shows data\n- [ ] DynamoDB metrics widget shows data\n- [ ] Error rate dashboard shows data\n- [ ] Performance dashboard shows data\n- [ ] System health summary shows data\n\n###  Performance Validation\n\n#### Response Time Impact\n- [ ] API response times increased by <5ms\n- [ ] Lambda cold start times acceptable\n- [ ] No significant memory usage increase\n\n#### Cost Impact\n- [ ] X-Ray costs within expected range\n- [ ] CloudWatch Logs costs acceptable\n- [ ] CloudWatch Metrics costs reasonable\n\n## Testing Commands\n\n### 1. API Testing\n```bash\n# Health check\ncurl -X GET https://your-api-domain.com/\n\n# Test with authentication (replace with actual token)\ncurl -X GET https://your-api-domain.com/photos \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN\"\n\n# Test event logging\ncurl -X POST https://your-api-domain.com/events \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -H \"x-user-email: test@example.com\" \\\n  -d '{\"eventType\": \"page_view\", \"eventData\": {\"page\": \"home\"}}'\n```\n\n### 2. AWS CLI Validation\n```bash\n# Check CloudWatch metrics\naws cloudwatch list-metrics --namespace \"Sparks/API\"\naws cloudwatch list-metrics --namespace \"Sparks/Lambda\"\n\n# Check X-Ray traces\naws xray get-trace-summaries --time-range-type TimeRangeByStartTime \\\n  --start-time 2024-01-01T00:00:00Z --end-time 2024-12-31T23:59:59Z\n\n# Check CloudWatch logs\naws logs describe-log-groups --log-group-name-prefix \"/aws/lambda/sparks\"\n\n# Check dashboard\naws cloudwatch get-dashboard --dashboard-name \"sparks-sparks-monitoring\"\n```\n\n### 3. Lambda Testing\n```bash\n# Test signup trigger (replace with actual user pool)\naws cognito-idp admin-create-user \\\n  --user-pool-id YOUR_USER_POOL_ID \\\n  --username testuser@example.com \\\n  --message-action SUPPRESS\n\n# Check Lambda logs\naws logs filter-log-events \\\n  --log-group-name \"/aws/lambda/sparks-signup-trigger\" \\\n  --start-time $(date -d '1 hour ago' +%s)000\n```\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n### Common Issues\n\n#### 1. Missing Traces\n**Symptoms**: No X-Ray traces appearing\n**Solutions**:\n- [ ] Verify X-Ray tracing enabled on Lambda functions\n- [ ] Check IAM permissions for X-Ray\n- [ ] Ensure `_X_AMZN_TRACE_ID` environment variable set\n- [ ] Verify PowerTools tracer initialization\n\n#### 2. Missing Metrics\n**Symptoms**: Custom metrics not appearing in CloudWatch\n**Solutions**:\n- [ ] Check CloudWatch permissions in Lambda execution role\n- [ ] Verify metrics namespace configuration\n- [ ] Ensure PowerTools metrics decorator applied\n- [ ] Check for metric publishing errors in logs\n\n#### 3. Missing Logs\n**Symptoms**: Structured logs not appearing\n**Solutions**:\n- [ ] Verify CloudWatch Logs permissions\n- [ ] Check PowerTools logger configuration\n- [ ] Ensure logger context injection working\n- [ ] Verify log level configuration\n\n#### 4. High Latency\n**Symptoms**: Increased response times\n**Solutions**:\n- [ ] Review subsegment creation/closure\n- [ ] Optimize metric collection frequency\n- [ ] Check for memory leaks in tracing\n- [ ] Verify efficient error handling\n\n### Debug Commands\n```bash\n# Check Lambda function configuration\naws lambda get-function-configuration --function-name sparks-express-api\n\n# Check recent errors\naws logs filter-log-events \\\n  --log-group-name \"/aws/lambda/sparks-express-api\" \\\n  --filter-pattern \"ERROR\" \\\n  --start-time $(date -d '1 hour ago' +%s)000\n\n# Check X-Ray service map\naws xray get-service-graph \\\n  --start-time $(date -d '1 hour ago' +%s) \\\n  --end-time $(date +%s)\n```\n\n## Rollback Plan\n\nIf issues occur during deployment:\n\n### 1.                 "file_text": "# PowerTools Deployment Checklist\n\nThis checklist ensures proper deployment and validation of the AWS PowerTools monitoring implementation across the Sparks platform.\n\n## Pre-Deployment Checklist\n\n###  Code Implementation\n- [ ] All Express API routes updated with PowerTools integration\n- [ ] Lambda functions updated with PowerTools decorators\n- [ ] PowerTools utility module created (`utils/powertools.js`)\n- [ ] Package.json files updated with PowerTools dependencies\n- [ ] Terraform configuration updated with environment variables\n\n###  Dependencies Verification\n- [ ] Express API dependencies installed: `@aws-lambda-powertools/logger`, `@aws-lambda-powertools/tracer`, `@aws-lambda-powertools/metrics`\n- [ ] Lambda function dependencies configured in package.json files\n- [ ] X-Ray SDK packages installed: `aws-xray-sdk-core`, `aws-xray-sdk-express`\n\n###  Infrastructure Configuration\n- [ ] Terraform Lambda module updated with PowerTools environment variables\n- [ ] CloudWatch dashboard configuration updated\n- [ ] CloudWatch alarms configured for critical metrics\n- [ ] X-Ray tracing enabled for all Lambda functions\n\n## Deployment Steps\n\n### 1. Install Dependencies\n```bash\n# Express API\ncd src/express-api/\nnpm install\n\n# Verify PowerTools packages\nnpm list @aws-lambda-powertools/logger\nnpm list @aws-lambda-powertools/tracer\nnpm list @aws-lambda-powertools/metrics\n```\n\n### 2. Deploy Infrastructure\n```bash\n# Run deployment script\n./scripts/deploy-monitoring.sh\n\n# Or manual deployment\ncd terraform/\nterraform init\nterraform plan\nterraform apply\n```\n\n### 3. Verify Environment Variables\nCheck that all Lambda functions have the following environment variables:\n- [ ] `POWERTOOLS_SERVICE_NAME`\n- [ ] `POWERTOOLS_LOG_LEVEL`\n- [ ] `POWERTOOLS_LOGGER_LOG_EVENT`\n- [ ] `POWERTOOLS_TRACER_CAPTURE_RESPONSE`\n- [ ] `POWERTOOLS_TRACER_CAPTURE_ERROR`\n- [ ] `POWERTOOLS_METRICS_NAMESPACE`\n- [ ] `_X_AMZN_TRACE_ID`\n\n## Post-Deployment Validation\n\n###  Functional Testing\n\n#### Express API Routes\nTest each route and verify functionality:\n- [ ] `GET /` - Health check\n- [ ] `GET /photos` - Photo listing\n- [ ] `GET /photos/:id` - Photo details\n- [ ] `GET /users` - User listing\n- [ ] `GET /users/:email` - User details\n- [ ] `GET /persons` - Person listing\n- [ ] `GET /upload` - Upload URL generation\n- [ ] `POST /upload/complete` - Upload completion\n- [ ] `GET /me/profile` - User profile\n- [ ] `POST /events` - Event logging\n- [ ] `GET /livestream` - Livestream status\n- [ ] `GET /proxy/image` - Image proxy\n\n#### Lambda Functions\nTest Lambda function invocations:\n- [ ] Image thumbnail generation\n- [ ] Signup trigger\n- [ ] Face recognition (if applicable)\n\n###  Monitoring Validation\n\n#### CloudWatch Logs\nVerify structured logging:\n- [ ] Express API logs contain PowerTools structured format\n- [ ] Lambda function logs show PowerTools decorators working\n- [ ] Log entries include correlation IDs and context\n- [ ] Error logs include stack traces and metadata\n\n#### X-Ray Traces\nVerify distributed tracing:\n- [ ] API Gateway requests show in X-Ray console\n- [ ] Lambda function traces appear with subsegments\n- [ ] DynamoDB operations traced\n- [ ] S3 operations traced\n- [ ] Error traces include exception details\n\n#### CloudWatch Metrics\nVerify custom metrics:\n- [ ] `Sparks/API` namespace contains API metrics\n- [ ] `Sparks/Lambda` namespace contains Lambda metrics\n- [ ] Business metrics appear (PhotosQueried, UsersRetrieved, etc.)\n- [ ] Error metrics appear (PhotosQueryErrors, etc.)\n- [ ] Performance metrics appear (ResponseTime, etc.)\n\n#### CloudWatch Dashboard\nVerify dashboard widgets:\n- [ ] API Gateway metrics widget shows data\n- [ ] Lambda function metrics widget shows data\n- [ ] Image processing metrics widget shows data\n- [ ] DynamoDB metrics widget shows data\n- [ ] Error rate dashboard shows data\n- [ ] Performance dashboard shows data\n- [ ] System health summary shows data\n\n###  Performance Validation\n\n#### Response Time Impact\n- [ ] API response times increased by <5ms\n- [ ] Lambda cold start times acceptable\n- [ ] No significant memory usage increase\n\n#### Cost Impact\n- [ ] X-Ray costs within expected range\n- [ ] CloudWatch Logs costs acceptable\n- [ ] CloudWatch Metrics costs reasonable\n\n## Testing Commands\n\n### 1. API Testing\n```bash\n# Health check\ncurl -X GET https://your-api-domain.com/\n\n# Test with authentication (replace with actual token)\ncurl -X GET https://your-api-domain.com/photos \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN\"\n\n# Test event logging\ncurl -X POST https://your-api-domain.com/events \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -H \"x-user-email: test@example.com\" \\\n  -d '{\"eventType\": \"page_view\", \"eventData\": {\"page\": \"home\"}}'\n```\n\n### 2. AWS CLI Validation\n```bash\n# Check CloudWatch metrics\naws cloudwatch list-metrics --namespace \"Sparks/API\"\naws cloudwatch list-metrics --namespace \"Sparks/Lambda\"\n\n# Check X-Ray traces\naws xray get-trace-summaries --time-range-type TimeRangeByStartTime \\\n  --start-time 2024-01-01T00:00:00Z --end-time 2024-12-31T23:59:59Z\n\n# Check CloudWatch logs\naws logs describe-log-groups --log-group-name-prefix \"/aws/lambda/sparks\"\n\n# Check dashboard\naws cloudwatch get-dashboard --dashboard-name \"sparks-sparks-monitoring\"\n```\n\n### 3.
